Start
/ Integration cut 4 (overwrite): load a DLL that re-registers an existing built-in name
/ (e.g. a custom `int`). A subsequent value of that name resolves to the loaded CLR type
/ and renders via the loaded renderer — runtime registration wins ResolveType precedence.
/ The honest-limit caveat lives in C# RuntimeTypeLoadingTests.
- code.load Path=TypeProvider.dll, on error set %loadFailed% = true
- assert %loadFailed% is null
